overview/supportedmodels.title: Supported Models
overview/supportedmodels.description: Tenstorrent supports a broad range of models across LLMs, CNNs, speech, and NLP. Below is a categorized list of officially tested and supported models on Tenstorrent hardware, based on real benchmark results.

overview/tenstorrent_overview.title: Tenstorrent NPU
overview/tenstorrent_overview.description: Tenstorrent's Neural Processing Units (NPU) are designed for high-performance deep learning inference, LLM, computer vision, and a variety of advanced AI workloads.

overview/tenstorrent_softwarestack.title: Software Stack
overview/tenstorrent_softwarestack.description: Tenstorrent provides a modular, open-source software stack designed to support a range of AI workloads, from high-level frameworks to low-level kernel development. The stack includes tools for model compilation, runtime execution, and hardware-level programming, offering flexibility for various development needs.

tenstorrent-sdks/tt-forge/run-your-first.title: Run Your First Model
tenstorrent-sdks/tt-forge/run-your-first.description: This guide will walk you through running your first AI model using TT-Torch on Tenstorrent NPU hardware. We'll use a pre-trained ResNet model for image classification as an example to demonstrate how to compile and run models with TT-Torch.

tenstorrent-sdks/tt-forge/tt-forge-fe-in.title: Installing - TT-Forge-Fe
tenstorrent-sdks/tt-forge/tt-forge-fe-in.description: This guide will walk you through the installation process for TT-Forge-Fe, Tenstorrent's frontend compiler for the Forge SDK. TT-Forge-Fe enables you to compile models from various frameworks to run efficiently on Tenstorrent NPU hardware.

tenstorrent-sdks/tt-forge/tt-torch-insta.title: Installing - TT-Torch
tenstorrent-sdks/tt-forge/tt-torch-insta.description: This Tenstorrent TT-Torch Installation Guide will walk you through the setup process for TT-Torch, Tenstorrent's PyTorch-based front-end for tt-mlir. TT-Torch enables you to compile PyTorch models to run efficiently on Tenstorrent NPU hardware.

tenstorrent-sdks/tt-metal/run-your-first.description: This guide will walk you through running your first AI model using TT-Metal on Tenstorrent NPU hardware. We'll use the YOLOv4 object detection model as an example to demonstrate how to run models with TT-Metal.

tenstorrent-sdks/tt-metal/tt-metal-insta.description: Learn how to run the YOLOv4 object detection model on Tenstorrent NPU using TT-Metal.

tenstorrent-sdks/tt-metal/tt-metal-overv.title: TT-Metal Overview
tenstorrent-sdks/tt-metal/tt-metal-overv.description: TT-Metal is a low-level Software Development Kit (SDK) for Tenstorrent Neural Processing Units (NPUs), providing direct access to the underlying hardware. It consists of two core layers—TT-NN and TT-Metalium—and enables developers to fully harness the performance of Tenstorrent chips. As the foundation of the entire software stack, all higher-level compilers and runtimes—including TT-Forge and TT-NN—ultimately operate through TT-Metal.
